<p>Cincinnati's four distinct seasons require proactive HVAC maintenance scheduling. Spring preparation should include cleaning outdoor condenser units, checking refrigerant levels, and testing cooling systems before summer heat arrives. Fall maintenance focuses on heating system inspections, furnace filter replacement, and ensuring heat pump defrost cycles function properly for winter operation. Winter monitoring includes checking for ice buildup on heat pump units and ensuring backup heating systems operate correctly during sub-freezing temperatures. Summer maintenance emphasizes cleaning evaporator coils and monitoring system performance during peak cooling demands when outdoor temperatures exceed 85¬∞F.</p>

